Nigeria Tightens Security Checks at Airports, ThisDay Reports

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-05T09:08:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/nigeria-tightens-security-checks-at-airports-thisday-reports.html
Nigeria tightened security checks at
all airports in the West African nation after U.S. forces killed
 Osama bin Laden ,  ThisDay reported , citing the director general
of the Nigeria  Civil Aviation Authority , Harold Demuren.  All passengers and luggage will undergo more intense
scrutiny, and the number of plainclothes detectives deployed at
airports has increased, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net . 